Name: Eccentric Heel Lowers
Description: Up with two legs, down on one. 5+ FULL breaths (1 exhale/lowering phase).

Name: 1 Knee Stretch w/ Band
Description: Maintain short foot in front foot. 5+ FULL breaths (1 exhale/stretch phase).

Name: 3 Way Wall Knee Drive
Description: Move forward and both diagonals with short foot in stationary foot. Exhale during stretch. 3+ each direction.

Name: 1 Knee Wall Stretch
Description: 2 phases: 1.) hands on ground, drive hips forward and down, can rotate shoulders either direction, 2.) get tall with exhale and reach of arm on down knee side, contract core and down side glute. 5+ FULL breaths (1 exhale/stretch phase).

Name: Split-Stance Bent-Over Stretch w/ Band
Description: Band around front leg high hip. Fold over thigh. Inhale with knee bend, exhale when straightening front leg while further folding over thigh. 5+ FULL breaths (1 exhale/stretch phase).

Name: Split-Stance Sink and Press w/ Band
Description: Band around back leg high hip. Sink down on inhale, exhale to get tall while contracting core and back side glute. Push down on band when getting tall. 5+ FULL breaths (1 exhale/stretch phase).

Name: Spiderman Hip Circles w/ Band
Description: In spiderman position, band around front leg high hip. Go into hip circles, moving slowly both clockwise and counterclockwise. 5+ FULL breaths (1 exhale/circle).

Name: Feet on Wall Reverse Figure 4
Description: Place one foot on wall and other foot on outside of that legs lower thigh. Inhale to start then while holding breath, push against resistance for a few seconds. Release contraction, exhale, and simultaneously move into a greater stretch. 5+ cycles.

Name: 1 Knee Internal Rotation Stretch w/ Band
Description: Have band around high hip and get into a push-up position. Place knee on ground of band side. Use partner or kettlebell to hold lower leg outside of knee. Inhale to start then while holding breath, push against resistance for a few seconds. Release contraction, exhale, and simultaneously move into a greater stretch. 5+ cycles.

Name: Elevated Pigeon
Description: Elevate lower leg, aiming to get shin parallel to shoulders. Have foot hanging off elevation. Inhale to start then while holding breath, push against resistance for a few seconds. Release contraction, exhale, and simultaneously move into a greater stretch. 5+ cycles.

Name: Elevated Straight Leg Stretch
Description: Elevate foot, keeping leg straight and torso tall. Inhale to start then while holding breath, push against resistance for a few seconds. Release contraction, exhale, and simultaneously move into a greater stretch. 5+ cycles.

Name: Deep Squat Hang
Description: Full exhale while pulling ribs down and tucking tailbone under

Name: Kneeling Dowel Stretch
Description: Deep exhale on stretch. Contract/Relax with breath to enhance stretch.  + band around elbows?

Name: 6 Way Ankle
Description: 3 Way Seated Ankle (Dorsiflexion, Inversion, Eversion) and 3 Way Calf Raise (In/Out/Neutral Calf Raise). x 10 each.

Name: Short Foot and Walking Drills
Description: Short Foot - grab ground w/ 3 points of contact (big toe, little toe, heel) and raise arch - x 5 reps. Walking Drills - on toes forward and backward, inversion and eversion forward.

Name: 2 Arm/1 Leg RDL Hold
Description: Hold Weight in Each Hand. x 5 Reps/Side (i.e. holds). 2 Breaths/Hold.

Name: Goblet Squat Hold
Description: Mini-Band Above Knees. x 5 Reps (i.e. holds). 2 Breaths/Hold.

Name: Straight Leg Lowers w/ Tubing
Description: Pull Band and Lower Leg on Exhale. x 5/Side.

Name: Mini-Band Series
Description: 1.) Sidewalks (band around base of toes), 2.) 3 Bucket (band around arches), 3.) Sprinter Start Leg Raise (band around ankles). x 10 each.

Name: 90/90 Bottom Up Kettlebell Walk
Description: Swing to get up. Shoulder and elbow at 90 degrees. Press elbow forward and out to side a bit. 2x20 steps each arm.

Name: Front Facing Wall Slides
Description: Short Split-Stance (Right Leg Forward). Slide at 135 deg. w/ Lift-Off. x 5.

Name: Prone T
Description: Chin on bench, each rep is one deep exhale. x 5.
